      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOVELY LAINEY (2) was drawn the middle last start but pinged the lids and recorded an all-the-way win (20.05) at Traralgon in a Grade 5 over 350m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. FREQUENCY (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Traralgon behind Yorkshire Girl (24.83) in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Leading player again. WARRIOR JACK (7) was in the minors two back (23.18) at this track but ran below best last time at Sale, finishing 6th. Has a good record here at this journey. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. SUPREME QUEEN (6) warrants respect following a recent placing over this course and distance.",
